title: USF rolls to 7-0 with rout of Concordia
text:
USF rolls to 7-0 with rout of Concordia 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 11:35 PM EDT 
FORT WAYNE, Ind. (21 ALive) - Nick Ferrer threw four more touchdown passes and Saint Francis finished with 45 straight points after trailing early to pound Concordia 48-7 Saturday. 
Ferrer threw two of his scoring passes to Cam Smith, and another to Seth Coate, who grabbed seven of Ferrer's passes for 148 yards.

Justin Green and P.J. Dean each ran for touchdowns and Ryan Nix added a pair of field goals for the Cougars, who moved to 7-0 and 5-0 in the Mid States Football Association Mideast League, clinching a share of the MEL title.
